      "title": "Just moved? First time voter? Coloradans can register to vote up...",
      "content_html": "\u003ca href=\"https://www.facebook.com/acluofcolorado/\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://scontent.fapa1-1.fna.fbcdn.net/v/t31.0-1/cp0/p50x50/21950661_1662566980443451_7358479861831904430_o.jpg?_nc_cat=103\u0026ccb=2\u0026_nc_sid=dbb9e7\u0026_nc_ohc=_hGxJau0kB0AX-KsA6Z\u0026_nc_ht=scontent.fapa1-1.fna\u0026tp=27\u0026oh=ad4eeb7cc360b40f4ed85dfea18c1c9f\u0026oe=5FC6BDFC\" alt=\"\" /\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.facebook.com/acluofcolorado/\"\u003eACLU of Colorado\u003c/a\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.facebook.com/acluofcolorado/photos/a.131340536899444/3699004133466382/\"\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.facebook.com\"\u003e\u003ci\u003e\u003c/i\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003cp\u003eJust moved? First time voter? Coloradans can register to vote up to and on Election Day. If you need to register to vote or update your voter registration information, you can still do so in-person at a Voter Service and Polling Center in your county.  \u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e Don't forget to bring one of 16 acceptable forms of ID, including Medicaid cards and utility bills: \u003ca href=\"https://www.sos.state.co.us/pubs/elections/vote/acceptableFormsOfID.html\"\u003ehttps://www.sos.state.co.us/…/elections/vote/acceptableForm…\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.facebook.com/acluofcolorado/photos/a.131340536899444/3699004133466382/\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://scontent.fapa1-1.fna.fbcdn.net/v/t1.0-0/s526x296/123338447_3699004140133048_3855764800623701011_o.jpg?_nc_cat=108\u0026ccb=2\u0026_nc_sid=8024bb\u0026_nc_ohc=7jHWUuducVEAX_fFsD0\u0026_nc_ht=scontent.fapa1-1.fna\u0026tp=7\u0026oh=b37de72041c02c5dc7bf503fe735926f\u0026oe=5FC67E15\" alt=\"Image may contain: text that says 'SAME-DAY REGISTRATION Available at any VSPC with one of the following forms of ID: Driver's license or state I.D. card U.S. passport Employee I.D. card from the state Pilot's license U.S military identification card -Utility bill, bank statement, government check, paycheck, or other gov. document from the last 60 days Certificate of Degree of Indian or Alaskan Native Blood Medicare or Medicaid card U.S. birth certificate Certified documentation of naturalization Student I.D. card Veteran I.D. card Tribal I.D. card ACLU Co'\" width=\"500\" height=\"262\" caption=\"Image may contain: text that says 'SAME-DAY REGISTRATION Available at any VSPC with one of the following forms of ID: Driver's license or state I.D. card U.S. passport Employee I.D. card from the state Pilot's license U.S military identification card -Utility bill, bank statement, government check, paycheck, or other gov. document from the last 60 days Certificate of Degree of Indian or Alaskan Native Blood Medicare or Medicaid card U.S. birth certificate Certified documentation of naturalization Student I.D. card Veteran I.D. card Tribal I.D. card ACLU Co'\" /\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.facebook.com/votinginformationcenter/\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/rsrc.php/v3/yw/r/uboafmf-0hy.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" /\u003eVisit the Voting Information Center for official election resources and local updates. Get Voting Information\u003c/a\u003e",
