      "title": "Denver is threatening public health by arbitrarily designating...",
      "content_html": "\u003ca href=\"https://www.facebook.com/acluofcolorado/\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://scontent.fapa1-1.fna.fbcdn.net/v/t31.0-1/cp0/p50x50/21950661_1662566980443451_7358479861831904430_o.jpg?_nc_cat=103\u0026ccb=2\u0026_nc_sid=dbb9e7\u0026_nc_ohc=_hGxJau0kB0AX-KsA6Z\u0026_nc_ht=scontent.fapa1-1.fna\u0026tp=27\u0026oh=ad4eeb7cc360b40f4ed85dfea18c1c9f\u0026oe=5FC6BDFC\" alt=\"\" /\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.facebook.com/acluofcolorado/\"\u003eACLU of Colorado\u003c/a\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.facebook.com/acluofcolorado/posts/3696635637036565\"\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.facebook.com\"\u003e\u003ci\u003e\u003c/i\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003cp\u003eDenver is threatening public health by arbitrarily designating public works cleanups without community support. Decisions about people experiencing homelessness should never be made without the input of people experiencing homelessness.\u003c/p\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.denvervoice.org/archive/2020/10/28/aclu-says-citys-regular-public-works-cleanups-violate-lyall-settlement\"\u003eStory by Robert Davis Photos by Giles Clasen The ACLU of Colorado has notified the Denver City Attorney’s Office (CAO) that the City is violating the terms of the Lyall settlement and threatening public health by arbitrarily designating two former homeless camp sites for “regular public works cl\u003cimg src=\"https://external.fapa1-1.fna.fbcdn.net/safe_image.php?d=AQBsj8uNVzbDW4L-\u0026w=540\u0026h=282\u0026url=http%3A%2F%2Fstatic1.squarespace.com%2Fstatic%2F58a88b0f3a0411800f07b1a1%2Ft%2F5f9a2ac4c9785a7f63effe7f%2F1603939093201%2FORDER_WEB.jpg%3Fformat%3D1500w\u0026cfs=1\u0026upscale=1\u0026fallback=news_d_placeholder_publisher\u0026_nc_cb=1\u0026_nc_hash=AQDghPFzXVAkWUwA\" alt=\"\" width=\"500\" height=\"262\" caption=\"\" /\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003cp\u003edenvervoice.org\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eACLU says City’s Regular Public Works Cleanups Violate Lyall Settlement — The Denver VOICE\u003c/p\u003eStory by Robert Davis Photos by Giles Clasen The ACLU of Colorado has notified the Denver City Attorney’s Office (CAO) that the City is violating the terms of the Lyall settlement and threatening public health by arbitrarily designating two former homeless camp sites for “regular public works cl\u003ca href=\"https://www.denvervoice.org/archive/2020/10/28/aclu-says-citys-regular-public-works-cleanups-violate-lyall-settlement\"\u003eStory by Robert Davis Photos by Giles Clasen The ACLU of Colorado has notified the Denver City Attorney’s Office (CAO) that the City is violating the terms of the Lyall settlement and threatening public health by arbitrarily designating two former homeless camp sites for “regular public works cl\u003c/a\u003e",
