      "title": "Risk assessment tools are used to decide who remains in jail....",
      "content_html": "\u003ca href=\"https://www.facebook.com/acluofcolorado/\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://scontent.fapa1-1.fna.fbcdn.net/v/t31.0-1/cp0/p50x50/21950661_1662566980443451_7358479861831904430_o.jpg?_nc_cat=103\u0026ccb=2\u0026_nc_sid=dbb9e7\u0026_nc_ohc=_hGxJau0kB0AX-KsA6Z\u0026_nc_ht=scontent.fapa1-1.fna\u0026tp=27\u0026oh=ad4eeb7cc360b40f4ed85dfea18c1c9f\u0026oe=5FC6BDFC\" alt=\"\" /\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.facebook.com/acluofcolorado/\"\u003eACLU of Colorado\u003c/a\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.facebook.com/acluofcolorado/photos/a.131340536899444/3696471500386312/\"\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.facebook.com\"\u003e\u003ci\u003e\u003c/i\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003cp\u003eRisk assessment tools are used to decide who remains in jail. The stakes couldn't be higher. Yet our research shows that they're dangerous, ineffective and racist. We can't automate decisions around liberty and freedom. Read the ACLU letter released today: \u003ca href=\"https://bit.ly/2G5RqyK\"\u003ehttps://bit.ly/2G5RqyK\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.facebook.com/acluofcolorado/photos/a.131340536899444/3696471500386312/\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://scontent.fapa1-2.fna.fbcdn.net/v/t1.0-9/s851x315/122993764_3696471503719645_2080467815313379913_o.jpg?_nc_cat=107\u0026ccb=2\u0026_nc_sid=8024bb\u0026_nc_ohc=axDZOkEf-RAAX-hdOqZ\u0026_nc_ht=scontent.fapa1-2.fna\u0026tp=7\u0026oh=f884c9a2668ba0573d45c9242d8fd23e\u0026oe=5FC55C89\" alt=\"Image may contain: text\" width=\"500\" height=\"313\" caption=\"Image may contain: text\" /\u003e\u003c/a\u003e",
      "date_published": "2020-10-29T13:39:38-06:00",
